<</A 5299 0 R/Alt( The figure shows a diagram labeled ŹTop View, at time t sub B.Ä The diagram shows two horizontal parallel rails at distance L apart. The rails are connected on their left ends by resistor R. There is an uncompressed spring between the rails, to the right of the resistor. The left end of the spring is fixed in place. A conducting bar is on top of the rails. Between the two rails and to the right of the spring, there are two regions with uniform magnetic fields of magnitude B. The uniform magnetic field in the region on the left is directed into the page and the uniform magnetic field in the region on the right is directed out of the page. The conducting bar is within the uniform magnetic field in the region on the left. )/ID(AD230404-1443-23.1.20143-ADBE-000000006400)/K 4/P 2798 0 R/Pg 113 0 R/S/Figure>>
